text: The 2026 South Australian state election will be held on 21 March 2026 to elect the 56th Parliament of South Australia, including all 47 seats in the House of Assembly and 11 of the 22 seats in the Legislative Council. It will be conducted by the Electoral Commission of South Australia (ECSA). The incumbent Labor government, led by Premier Peter Malinauskas, will be trying to win a second term in government. They will be opposed by the Liberal Party, led by David Speirs. ==References== Category:2026 elections Category:Elections in South Australia Category:2020s in Australia
title: 2026 South Australian state election
